Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising
5.8
AdvertisementBy JEANNETTE CATSOULIS“Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising” Proudly crass and amiably dumb, A sorority moves next door to parents Mac and Kelly, who turn to their former nemeses from the Delta Psi Beta fraternity to help battle the wild young women.But rejecting the gluten-free goals and eye-candy grooming of the sorority machine doesn’t make you a feminist, and objectification is no less offensive when you’re doing it in flats. Yet “Neighbors 2” doesn’t pretend to be taking a stand for women’s — or anyone’s — rights; its identity politics are scattershot at best, and its sympathies are with everyone.Most of all, perhaps, they’re with Teddy (JEANNETTE CATSOULIS“Neighbors 2: Sorority Rising” is rated R (Under 17 requires accompanying parent or adult guardian). A hail of tampons and a dildo dressed as a princess. 





